init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the "Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Dan was watching the news when the anchorwoman, a young woman who had been with the station for about a year, suddenly froze.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She was frozen in place, her eyes wide and her mouth slightly open.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I'm sorry, we have breaking news.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: His wife, his children, his grandchildren.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Dan was suddenly filled with rage.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He wrote a note to his children, telling them how much he loved them, and how he was sorry that he couldn't be there to help them
